1. Early labor: characterized by mild contractions, softening, and dilation of the cervix;
2. Active labor: stronger contractions and rapid dilation of the cervix (up to 10 cm);
3. Transition phase: the most intense contractions, leading to complete dilation of the cervix;
4. Pushing and birth of the baby: the mother pushes and delivers the baby;
5. Delivery of the placenta: the placenta is expelled from the uterus after birth.
